
Overview of noun threat

The noun threat has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (16) menace, threat -- (something that is a source of danger; "earthquakes are a constant threat in Japan")
2. (4) threat -- (a warning that something unpleasant is imminent; "they were under threat of arrest")
3. (4) threat -- (declaration of an intention or a determination to inflict harm on another; "his threat to kill me was quite explicit")
4. terror, scourge, threat -- (a person who inspires fear or dread; "he was the terror of the neighborhood")
